The article discusses President Trump's stance on the relationship between the United States and Saudi Arabia in light of the murder of journalist Jamal Khashoggi. Trump emphasizes the importance of the partnership with Saudi Arabia in countering Iran and fighting terrorism. He also highlights the economic benefits of the relationship, including Saudi Arabia's investment in the United States. Trump acknowledges the murder of Khashoggi as a terrible crime and sanctions individuals involved, but leaves open the possibility that the Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia may have had knowledge of the event. Trump states that the United States will continue to prioritize its own security and interests, and implies that any actions taken against Saudi Arabia should be consistent with this goal.